    <item>
      <title>PMT signal combiner</title>
      <link>https://sussex-neuroscience.github.io/project/pmt-combiner/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 03 Aug 2020 11:02:20 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://sussex-neuroscience.github.io/project/pmt-combiner/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This project got started when there was the need to combine the signals coming out
of two photo multiplier tubes (PMTs) installed in one of the 2-photon microscopes at the microscopy unit in Sussex Neuroscience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The particular PMTs installed were models 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.thorlabs.com/thorproduct.cfm?partnumber=PMT2101/M&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;PM2101&lt;/a&gt; from Thorlabs. This means that they are actually a &amp;ldquo;combo&amp;rdquo; of PMT plus current to voltage converter, and the output signal from the unit is voltage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More technical details can be found on the project repository: &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/sussex-neuroscience/pmt-combiner/&#34;&gt;https://github.com/sussex-neuroscience/pmt-combiner/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
